messages.message:
Patch Set 1:

The matching kernel changes: https://github.com/airend/android_kernel_bn_omap/commits/3.4/nookhd, so basically, OZ upstream is still default remoteproc/rpmsg implementation w/o CONFIG_USE_AMAZON_DUCATI.

Patch Set 1: Verified+1 Code-Review+1

The other option is to keep the lighter firmware in vendor/bn (http://gerrit.unlegacy-android.cf/#/q/topic:amz-xem3-opt2). Although I think it belongs here (should work on espresso, has some camera support, etc), the other location is equal to me.
Patch Set 2: Published edit on patch set 1.

Patch Set 2:

(1 comment)

We still have to carefully decide if we keep this alternative firmware here. It's a major improvement on my 1080p device. I don't know if the AMZ camera support could be made to work on espresso, but then again, Blaze Ducati is even worse there…
Change has been successfully merged by Dániel Járai
